  <title>OCCI Application</title>

  <para>The OCCI Application specification defines kinds and extensions
  relating to management of cloud application services (SaaS).</para>

  <table>
    <title>Common Attributes</title>

    <tgroup cols="3">
      <colspec align="center" />

      <thead>
        <row>
          <entry align="left">Attribute</entry>

          <entry>Type</entry>

          <entry>Description</entry>
        </row>
      </thead>

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry
          align="left"><computeroutput>occi.application.version</computeroutput></entry>

          <entry>Float (e.g. 1.0)</entry>

          <entry>Version of the OCCI Application specification</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </table>

  <section>
    <title>Kinds</title>

    <para>Cloud application services can be modeled using the following
    primary kinds:</para>

    <table>
      <title>Kinds</title>

      <tgroup cols="3">
        <colspec align="center" />

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry align="left">Kind</entry>

            <entry>URI</entry>

            <entry>Description</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry
            align="left"><computeroutput>contact</computeroutput></entry>

            <entry><uri>http://purl.org/occi/kind/contact</uri></entry>

            <entry>A contact; a person, a venue such as a club or a
            restaurant, or an organisation.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry
            align="left"><computeroutput>document</computeroutput></entry>

            <entry><uri>http://purl.org/occi/kind/document</uri></entry>

            <entry>A word processing document</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry align="left"><computeroutput>event</computeroutput></entry>

            <entry><uri>http://purl.org/occi/kind/event</uri></entry>

            <entry>A calendar event</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry
            align="left"><computeroutput>presentation</computeroutput></entry>

            <entry><uri>http://purl.org/occi/kind/presentation</uri></entry>

            <entry>A visual representation</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry
            align="left"><computeroutput>spreadsheet</computeroutput></entry>

            <entry><uri>http://purl.org/occi/kind/spreadsheet</uri></entry>

            <entry>A worksheet</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>

    <section>
      <title>Contact</title>

      <para>A contact is a person, venue, organisation, etc.</para>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Extensions</title>

    <para>Various extensions provide for more advanced management
    functionality such as billing, monitoring and reporting.</para>
  </section>

